#!/usr/bin/env bash
# bin/ai — PATH-shim ERROR STUB.
#
# Per SPEC.md §15 the `ai` binary lives on the system PATH via
# brew / scoop / winget (NOT in ~/.ai/bin/). This shim exists ONLY to
# catch the case where ~/.ai/bin/ accidentally precedes the system
# package's install location on PATH.
#
# If you're seeing this message, your PATH has ~/.ai/bin/ before the
# directory that holds the real `ai` binary. Fix by either:
#
#   1. (Recommended) Remove ~/.ai/bin/ from PATH and install via the
#      system package manager (`brew install convergent-systems-co/tap/ai`).
#
#   2. (Quick fix) Move the install location ahead of ~/.ai/bin/ in
#      your shell rc.

cat >&2 <<'EOF'
[ai] ERROR: ~/.ai/bin/ai is an error stub, not the binary.

Per SPEC.md §15, the `ai` binary lives on the system PATH via
brew / scoop / winget. Install it with:

  macOS / Linux: brew install convergent-systems-co/tap/ai
  Windows:       scoop install ai
                 (or: winget install convergent-systems-co.ai)

Or build from source:

  cd <your-aiConstitution-checkout>
  make build      # produces dist/ai
  cp dist/ai /usr/local/bin/ai   # or wherever you keep tools

Then ensure ~/.ai/bin/ does NOT appear before the install location on
your PATH.

If you intended to invoke a wrapper command (git / gh / etc.),
those wrappers ARE meant to live in ~/.ai/bin/ — they have different
filenames (~/.ai/bin/git, ~/.ai/bin/gh).
EOF
exit 1
